---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Three flights, one night in Tel Aviv — Trove Collections">
  <article class="story">
    <p class="muted breadcrumb"><a href="/stories">← Stories</a></p>

    <h1>Three flights, one night in Tel Aviv</h1>
    <p class="byline muted">by Eris &middot; <em>Levant</em></p>

    <figure class="story-image">
      <img
        src="/images/stories/tlv-arrival.jpg"
        alt="Tanya, Micki in uniform, and Cheryl Lynne in a Tel Aviv hotel lobby — Micki just in from the airport."
        width="1200"
        height="1600"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <figcaption class="muted">
        The lobby, minutes after my mom's arrival. Still in uniform, suitcase just
        out of frame.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      My mom, Tanya, and Cheryl Lynne have been friends for thirty years.
      Pilot friendships run on a strange clock &mdash; you can be best friends
      and see each other twice a year, because one of you is always somewhere
      over an ocean. The group chat never stops, but the same city, the same
      night? That takes the schedule gods.
    </p>

    <p>
      Then one night the schedule gods got playful. All three of them landed in
      Tel Aviv on the same evening &mdash; three separate flights, three
      different starting points, one hotel. After thirty years of friendship,
      the planet finally folded itself in exactly the right way.
    </p>

    <figure class="story-image">
      <img
        src="/images/stories/tlv-closeup.jpg"
        alt="Tanya, Micki, and Cheryl Lynne, close together and laughing in the hotel lobby."
        width="1200"
        height="1368"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption class="muted">Thirty years of friendship in one frame.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      My mom was the last one in &mdash; the lobby photos are her straight off
      the airplane, wings still on. There was just enough time to get out of
      uniform before dinner. The next morning they scattered across the planet
      again, the way pilots do, like it was nothing.
    </p>

    <figure class="story-image">
      <img
        src="/images/stories/tlv-dinner.jpg"
        alt="The three friends at dinner in the hotel — Coca-Cola bottle, limonana, and the flags of the lobby behind them."
        width="1200"
        height="1145"
        loading="lazy"
      />
      <figcaption class="muted">
        Dinner. A glass-bottle Coke, a limonana, and exactly one night to catch up on.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      These are the fairy godmothers &mdash; the family friends whose finds sit
      alongside my aunts' all over this site. Tanya curates our Italian picks;
      Cheryl Lynne's finds are scattered through the collections. When we say
      every item here was carried home by someone who flies, these are the
      women we mean. Sometimes the suitcase comes home from Lake Como.
      Sometimes it comes home with a story like this one.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <p class="muted" style="text-align: center;">
      <a href="/collections/levant">See the Levant Collection →</a>
      <br /><br />
      <a href="/about">Meet the whole circle →</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .story { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .breadcrumb { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--muted); border: 0; }
  .byline { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .story-image { margin: 2rem 0; }
  .story-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .story-image figcaption {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
